    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the ukiyo-e school or style associated with the Kamigata region of Japan, which varies from its Edo counterpart. Kamigata-e works depicting kabuki performers exhibit less idealized, and more specific portraits of individual actors. </Note_Text>
